; there remain some fifty pages to write, and I must be allowed to do so at my own pace. I can only say that LATH is a multiple-love story and that during a span of fifty years the scene shifts from my desk to Old Russia, from there to England, from England to France, from France to America and thence to Bolshevisia and back to this lake.

Cordially yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: ALEKSANDR SOLZHENITSYN1

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Palace Hotel

Montreux,

Suisse

14.II.1974

Dear Aleksandr Isaevic